### Instruction:
in javascript how do you save to and read back from localstorage

### Response:

To save data to local storage in JavaScript, you can use the `localStorage` object. Here's an example of how you might save a string value to local storage:
```
// Save a string value to local storage
localStorage.setItem("key", "value");

// Check if the item exists
if (localStorage.getItem("key")) {
  // The item exists, retrieve its value
  var storedValue = localStorage.getItem("key");

  // Do something with the retrieved value
}
```
To read data from local storage in JavaScript, you can use the `localStorage` object. Here's an example of how you might retrieve a string value from local storage:
```
// Check if the item exists
if (localStorage.getItem("key")) {
  // The item exists, retrieve its value
  var storedValue = localStorage.getItem("key");

  // Do something with the retrieved value
}
```
